The Nervii, a people of great eourage, awaited the arrival of Caesar’s army across the river. The Romans had chosen a hill on this side of the river for their camp. The enemy, however, suddenly attacked the soldiers who were fortifying this place. There was a fierce battle in which Caesar himself fought in the first rank. After the Nervii were defeated, Caesar stormed a town of the Aduatuci, who quiekly asked for mercy. And SO, having subdued all Gaul, he set out to Italy.
